description: After applying the security update corresponding to KB5033375 for Windows 11 Version 23H2 (build number 10.0.22631.2861), users may notice that certain system-level privileges can be unexpectedly elevated. This could lead to unauthorized access and control over systems, as the update addresses an elevation of privilege issue. The affected systems, particularly x64-based and ARM64-based, require immediate attention to mitigate potential risks posed by elevated privileges granted to exploited accounts.
